description: Test if the load module's indicator lamp receives voltage and turns on with all switches on. This will help determine if any current reaches the end of the circuit., outcome='No voltage was measured at the Internal Indicator Lamp (0.0 V at both terminals), and the lamp is not lit. This indicates that no current or voltage is reaching the lamp with all switches on. No observable internal faults were found in the lamp.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Output terminals of power supply module,
description: Measure the voltage between the two output terminals of the power supply module to verify that 12V is actually being supplied to the first control module., outcome="The voltage measured at 'PSU Output Cable (+)' is 11.9893 V, and at 'PSU Output Cable (−)' is 0.0 V, both with respect to ground. This confirms an expected voltage difference of approximately 12V between the output terminals of the power supply module. No polarity inversion is indicated in these measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Input terminals of Control Module 1,
description: Measure the voltage at the input terminals of Control Module 1 to verify that 12V is reaching the first control module., outcome='The voltage at Control Input Cable (+) 1 is 11.99 V, and at Control Input Cable (−) 1 is 0.0 V with respect to ground. No polarity inversion is detected based on these measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Output terminals of Control Module 1,
description: Measure the voltage at the output terminals of Control Module 1 to determine if voltage is being delivered through the first control module toward the subsequent modules., outcome="Voltage at 'Control Output Cable (+) 1' is 11.9893 V with respect to ground. Voltage at 'Control Output Cable (−) 1' is 0.0 V with respect to ground. No polarity inversion detected in these measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Input terminals of Control Module 2,
description: Measure the voltage at the input terminals of Control Module 2 to confirm if the 12V is being passed from Control Module 1 to Control Module 2 correctly., outcome='The voltage at Control Input Cable (+) 2 is 11.99 V, and at Control Input Cable (−) 2 is 0.0 V. These measurements confirm the presence of a voltage difference across the input terminals of Control Module 2. No polarity inversion is indicated by these results.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control Module 2 Output Terminals,
description: Measure the voltage at the output terminals of Control Module 2 to determine if the correct voltage is being passed to Control Module 3. This will help identify where the voltage is lost, if at all, through the sequence of modules., outcome='Voltage at Control Output Cable (+) 2 is 11.9893 V and at Control Output Cable (−) 2 is 0.0 V, both measured with respect to ground. Measured voltages are consistent and there is no polarity inversion reported in this step.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Input terminals of Control Module 3,
description: Measure the voltage at the input terminals of Control Module 3 to confirm the 12V is being properly delivered from Control Module 2., outcome='Voltage at Control Input Cable (+) 3 is 11.9893 V, and voltage at Control Input Cable (−) 3 is 0.0 V. The input terminals of Control Module 3 are receiving nearly 12V as expected. No polarity inversion detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control Module 3 output terminals,
description: Measure the voltage at the output terminals of Control Module 3 to verify that voltage is passed through to the next module and to continue narrowing down the location of the open circuit or fault., outcome='Both the Control Output Cable (+) 3 and Control Output Cable (−) 3 show 0.0 V with respect to ground. No voltage is being output from Control Module 3 at either terminal.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control Module 3 Internal Switch and Wiring,
description: With the system powered, measure voltage across the switch terminals inside Control Module 3 (both across the switch and at both sides to ground) with the switch in the ON position. This will help determine if the switch is internally faulty or if there is a wiring break within the module., outcome="Summary: The (+) input cable to Control Switch 3 is disconnected at port 'n', leaving it floating. All voltage readings at the switch and its output cables are 0 V, except at the disconnected end of the input (+) cable where 11.99 V is present. No polarity inversion detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=110.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
